						<summary>

						<p>On the north, <hi rend="italic">bhiṭṭi,</hi> Bhikshāṇḍār shrine, Śivayōganāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 14: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. Records that an individual, Puḻudiyūr-uḍaiyāṉ Tiruviśalūran Sūryaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Edirmeṟṟikaṇḍa-pēraraiyaṉ is stated to have made a donation (what was donated is obscured in the damaged portion) for burning a perpetual lamp to the god of (Tiruviśalūr in) Amaṉinārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa-brahmadēyam</hi> on the northern bank.</p>						

